      "role": "user",
      "content": "the manual tracking sounds like it's going to be a nightmare to implement across the whole codebase without introducing more bugs itself. i'm worried about missing something small that's just sitting there eating up bytes. are there any specific common patterns or \"sneaky\" places in C++ where these kinds of leaks tend to hide? like, specifically in embedded systems where you're dealing with interrupts or real-time tasks?",
      "source": "evaluator"
